CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1956, pg. A15, reads: "Steelworkers Idled by Strike - Plants Closed Down - ...In right photo, three salaried employes [employees] are shown inside the large Homestead works of U. S. Steel. The solitary picket outside the gates said, 'I don't want publicity.' - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Amity Street entrance gate of U.S. Steel Homestead Steel Works, during strike, with banner in background reading "Safety Comes First in This Plant, Know Your Safety Rules," Homestead
